The core of the issue seems to be related to how PHI nodes are handled when loops are fused, especially LCSSA PHI nodes. The reproducer shows two adjacent loops. The exit block of the first loop (`for.end`) contains an LCSSA PHI node (`%sum1.0.lcssa`). This block becomes part of the second loop's body after fusion.

The stack trace points to `LoopFuser::performFusion` in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopFuse.cpp`. This is where the fusion logic is implemented. The problem likely lies in how the pass remaps uses of values from the first loop to the second loop after merging them.

Specifically, when the exit block of the first loop is merged into the second loop, the LCSSA PHI node within it (`%sum1.0.lcssa`) becomes a regular PHI node. Its predecessors change. The `loop-fusion` pass must correctly update the incoming blocks for this PHI node. The crash suggests this is not happening correctly.

